", "text": "(Msb, TA;) also called ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamorN raTiybN", "text_ar": "تَمْرٌ رَطِيبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muroTibN", "text_ar": "مُرْطِبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muraT~ibN", "text_ar": "مُرَطِّبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) the dates so called are well known: (S:) [it is a coll. gen, n.:] n. un. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, Mgh, Msb, K:) it is not a broken pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruTabapN", "text_ar": "رُطَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", being masc. [as well as fem.] like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamorN", "text_ar": "تَمْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA ruTabN", "text_ar": "هٰذَا رُطَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "These are fresh ripe dates"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; whereas, if it were a broken pl., you would make it [only] fem.: (Sb, TA:) its pl. [of pauc.] is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroTaAbN", "text_ar": "اَرْطَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb) and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riTaAbN", "text_ar": "رِطَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and the pl. of the n. un. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruTabaAtN", "text_ar": "رُطَبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) There are two sorts of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruTab", "text_ar": "رُطَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": one sort cannot be dried, and spoils if not soon eaten: the other sort dries, and is made into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eajowap", "text_ar": "عَجْوَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]. (Msb.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "busorN", "text_ar": "بُسْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["A", "Mgh", "Msb", "K", "TA", "S", "Sb"]}]},